1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:03,287
Many systems jump straight to five agents in a meeting.

2
00:00:03,287 --> 00:00:05,509
The first step may already be wrong.

3
00:00:05,509 --> 00:00:12,824
Anthropic says the basic building block is an augmented LLM: one model enhanced with retrieval, tools, and memory.

4
00:00:12,824 --> 00:00:18,379
Retrieval finds the outside facts needed right now, so the model is not answering only from memory.

5
00:00:18,379 --> 00:00:24,108
Tools let the model query systems or take actions, turning text judgment into real operations.

6
00:00:24,108 --> 00:00:30,358
Memory keeps the state that actually matters across steps, so the system does not restart from zero every time.

7
00:00:30,358 --> 00:00:37,534
Example: a support agent checks an order, calls a refund tool, and remembers what the user already confirmed.

8
00:00:37,534 --> 00:00:40,486
The point is not to stuff in every capability.

9
00:00:40,486 --> 00:00:43,900
Keep the interfaces clear and the context just enough.

10
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:46,956
Tiny Rule: augment one model first.

11
00:00:46,956 --> 00:00:51,550
Split into multiple agents only when the responsibilities truly conflict.

12
00:00:51,550 --> 00:00:53,101
Follow Tiny Agent.

13
00:00:53,101 --> 00:00:55,833
Learn one AI agent idea every day.
